data.content:
In **.NET 11, the Cosmos DB provider completely removes sync I/O** — the `.EnableSyncIO()` opt-in you had in .NET 10 no longer works. All your synchronous calls (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) will **always throw at runtime**.

**Fix:** Convert everything to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

There is no workaround or opt-in to restore sync behavior in EF Core 11. All callers of these methods must also be updated to `await` the results (async propagates up the call stack).
